    • Field Detail

      • kFatalError

        public static final InformationalElement.InformationalType kFatalError
        A fatal error has occurred. This can occur when performing validation or as a result of an exception that did not relate to validation. An error of this type means that no further validations should be performed, the operation will fail and the user should be informed to allow them to fix the errors.

      • kError

        public static final InformationalElement.InformationalType kError
        An error has occurred when performing validation. An informational of this type means further validations will be performed even though the operation will eventually fail. The user should be informed at the end of execution to allow them to fix the errors.

      • kWarning

        public static final InformationalElement.InformationalType kWarning
        A warning has occurred when performing validation. An informational of this type means further validations should be performed. Providing no errors of a more serious kind are discovered the user should be informed of the warnings.
